    "urn:li:comment:(activity:7455265734013779968,7458557903176794112)": {
      "comment_urn": "urn:li:comment:(activity:7455265734013779968,7458557903176794112)",
      "commented_at": "2026-05-08T16:46:17Z",
      "verb": "commented",
      "text": "A few months ago I argued we should be storing prompts, not code. Reading this, I'd put it differently now — prompts drift too. The durable artifact is a structured spec, not a free-form prompt 👏\n\nWhen CodeSpeak lets me write the user behavior — and frees me from deciding how the modules connect to each other — that's the killer move.",
      "comment_author_name": "Peter Ovchynnikov",
      "comment_author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ovchyn",
      "post_urn": "urn:li:activity:7458557922441289728",
      "post_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7458557922441289728/",
      "post_author_name": "Andrey Breslav",
      "post_author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/abreslav",
      "permalink": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7458557922441289728/?commentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Acomment%3A%28activity%3A7455265734013779968%2C7458557903176794112%29",
      "weeks": {}
    },
    "urn:li:comment:(activity:7457076059105067008,7457093632718684160)": {
      "comment_urn": "urn:li:comment:(activity:7457076059105067008,7457093632718684160)",
      "commented_at": "2026-05-04T15:47:48Z",
      "verb": "commented",
      "text": "Thank you Kate. :)",
      "comment_author_name": "Peter Ovchynnikov",
      "comment_author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ovchyn",
      "post_urn": "urn:li:activity:7457093637747687425",
      "post_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7457093637747687425/",
      "post_author_name": "Kate Chapman",
      "post_author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/untanglingsystems",
      "permalink": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7457093637747687425/?commentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Acomment%3A%28activity%3A7457076059105067008%2C7457093632718684160%29",
      "weeks": {}
    },
    "urn:li:comment:(activity:7454892308568764417,7454921304845189123)": {
      "comment_urn": "urn:li:comment:(activity:7454892308568764417,7454921304845189123)",
      "commented_at": "2026-04-28T15:55:44Z",
      "verb": "commented",
      "text": "A technology becomes \"infrastructure\" not when everyone uses it 🤔 — it becomes infrastructure the moment something else breaks when it's down. AI crossed that line in 2025, and most of us only really noticed when the bill arrived.\n\nThis isn't a new pattern — everyone knew Postgres mattered, but nobody really tested failover until the first painful weekend. GitLab's 2017 postmortem is the classic public version of it (https://about.gitlab.com/blog/2017/02/10/postmortem-of-database-outage-of-january-31/) ⚙️.\n\nThat's why we've been building https://awesome-mcp.xyz — our portable abstraction layer over AI vendors, for easy switching between providers when we need to.\n\nModels keep getting better. The more interesting work happening right now is in the layer around them — recovery, support, exit paths, an actual human on the other end of the contract 🚀. Probably where the next decade lands.",
      "comment_author_name": "Peter Ovchynnikov",
      "comment_author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ovchyn",
      "post_urn": "urn:li:activity:7454921309119078400",
      "post_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7454921309119078400/",
      "post_author_name": "Nick Gluzdov",
      "post_author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/gluzd",
      "permalink": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7454921309119078400/?commentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Acomment%3A%28activity%3A7454892308568764417%2C7454921304845189123%29",
      "weeks": {}
    },
    "urn:li:comment:(activity:7452399627221409792,7452457086497570816)": {
      "comment_urn": "urn:li:comment:(activity:7452399627221409792,7452457086497570816)",
      "commented_at": "2026-04-21T20:43:49Z",
      "verb": "commented",
      "text": "Funny. I spent two years competing with OpenAI using a team of 5 and a $30K budget — and winning. Not because we evolved faster.\n\nBecause our client's enterprise had full immunity to adopting ChatGPT. Sometimes the antibody is a 47-page procurement process.",
      "comment_author_name": "Peter Ovchynnikov",
      "comment_author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ovchyn",
      "post_urn": "urn:li:activity:7452457104751280128",
      "post_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7452457104751280128/",
      "post_author_name": "Olga Mykhailova (Michai)",
      "post_author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/olga-mykhailova-michai-58b5424b",
      "permalink": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7452457104751280128/?commentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Acomment%3A%28activity%3A7452399627221409792%2C7452457086497570816%29",
      "weeks": {}
    },
    "urn:li:comment:(activity:7450893034742861824,7452356364816871425)": {
      "comment_urn": "urn:li:comment:(activity:7450893034742861824,7452356364816871425)",
      "commented_at": "2026-04-21T14:03:35Z",
      "verb": "commented",
      "text": "When I started building with AI in 2018, we called these people \"full-stack product engineers\" and nobody wrote LinkedIn posts about them being in demand 😄\n\nWhat changed is that AI removed the excuse. Before, you could always say \"we don't have capacity for polish, let's ship and iterate.\" Now you have the capacity — AI gives you all the speed you need. So when your product still feels clunky, it's a taste problem, not a resource problem.\n\nAnd suddenly everyone notices who has taste and who doesn't 🎯",
      "comment_author_name": "Peter Ovchynnikov",
      "comment_author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ovchyn",
      "post_urn": "urn:li:activity:7452356409469353984",
      "post_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7452356409469353984/",
      "post_author_name": "Gergely Orosz",
      "post_author_url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/gergelyorosz",
      "permalink": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7452356409469353984/?commentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Acomment%3A%28activity%3A7450893034742861824%2C7452356364816871425%29",
      "weeks": {}
    },
